  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (expanded envelope)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). NOTE: The clinical use case has grown since the original validation campaign; the device is now routinely deployed in paediatric perfusion circuits and at extended low-flow states (0.5–1.2 L/min) that were not represented in the 2019 validation dataset. No re-calibration or supplemental validation evidence covering this expanded operating envelope has been linked to this package.",
