      "rationale": "Three-level mesh refinement study (3.2 M, 8.7 M, 22.1 M cells) yields GCI = 1.8% for RH index at the nominal adult operating point. Richardson extrapolation applied. Study conducted at 2019 adult flow conditions only; no GCI study performed for low-flow or paediatric envelope."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental boundary conditions (inlet velocity, outlet pressure, fluid temperature, haematocrit) match simulation inputs within stated uncertainty bounds.",
      "rationale": "In-vitro loop conditions documented: bovine blood at 35 ± 0.5 °C, Hct 33 ± 1%, flow rates set by calibrated Coriolis meter (±0.5%). Boundary conditions replicated in CFD within measurement uncertainty. Conditions representative of adult CPB; paediatric haematocrit ranges (40–45%) and lower viscosity profiles not tested."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Predicted RH index within 15% of measured value across all validated operating points; systematic bias < 5%.",
      "rationale": "CFD RH index predictions agree with in-vitro measurements within 8% (max) and 4% (mean) across the five adult operating points. Systematic bias of 2.1% (over-prediction) noted. Acceptance criterion met for the 2019 validated range. No measured data available for low-flow or paediatric operating points to perform analogous comparison."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Primary QoI (relative hemolysis index, RH) is directly linked to clinical endpoint; secondary QoIs (shear stress distribution, exposure time) support mechanistic interpretation.",
      "rationale": "RH index is the regulatory-accepted surrogate for pump-induced hemolysis per FDA guidance. Volume-averaged scalar shear stress and Lagrangian particle exposure time tracked as supporting QoIs. QoI selection reviewed and confirmed appropriate for both adult and — by engineering judgement only — paediatric use, though no paediatric experimental comparator exists."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation activities cover the primary operating envelope defined in the COU; any gaps between validation conditions and COU conditions are documented and justified.",
      "rationale": "Validation activities conducted in 2019 cover the adult CPB flow regime (2.0–6.0 L/min) that constituted the original COU. The COU has since expanded to include paediatric circuits and low-flow states (0.5–1.2 L/min). This gap is noted; the team asserts by engineering analogy that turbulence model performance is expected to remain adequate, but no re-validation evidence in the expanded range has been generated or linked. Achieved level assessed as 2 based on original validation scope."
    },
